Robert Bates, 73, appeared in Tulsa district court on Tuesday and pleaded not guilty to second-degree manslaughter over the death of Eric Harris, 44 .
In 2009, the Tulsa Sheriff's Office concluded that Bates had received special treatment during training and while working as a reserve deputy, he told other deputies he could do whatever he wanted to do .
Bates shot Harris as he fled the scene of an undercover operation and faces four years in prison if convicted .